President Muhammadu Buhari has forwarded the 2020-2022 Medium Term Expenditure Framework, MTEF, and Fiscal Strategy Paper, FSP,   to the National Assembly for considerations and approval. The fiscal document was received and read in the Senate and House of Representatives by the Senate President, Ahmad Lawan and Deputy Speaker, Ahmed Wase at plenary. According to him, the key thrusts of the 2020 - 2022 MTEF/FSP include sustaining growth and diversifying the productive base of the economy, in line with the nation's Economic Recovery and Growth Plan. He added that the Government strived to ensure that forecasted revenues were not only realistic, but also reasonably challenging in the face of its significantly constrained fiscal space.  Our Correspondent, Raliat Adenekan reports that the Budget and Finance Ministry, the budget was based on oil production capacity of 2.18 million barrels per day (mbpd), crude Oil price of $55 per barrel, exchange rate of N305 to $1, average inflation rate of 10.8%, Gross Domestic Product of N142.96 trillion and growth rate of 2.9%.